.TH "dwc2_hsotg_ep_sethalt" 9 "dwc2_hsotg_ep_sethalt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dwc2_hsotg_ep_sethalt \- set halt on a given endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dwc2_hsotg_ep_sethalt
.BI "(struct usb_ep *ep "  ","
.BI "int value "  ","
.BI "bool now "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
The endpoint to set halt.
.IP "value" 12
Set or unset the halt.
.IP "now" 12
If true, stall the endpoint now. Otherwise return -EAGAIN if
the endpoint is busy processing requests.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
We need to stall the endpoint immediately if request comes from set_feature
protocol command handler.
